article.headline: Northern Arizona 63, Montana State 57
article.story: FLAGSTAFF, Ariz. (AP) -- Kelly Golob scored 17 points as Northern Arizona overcame one of its worst shooting efforts of the season to beat Montana State 63-57 on Saturday night -- its fourth straight victory. The Lumberjacks, the Big Sky's top offensive team, entered the game shooting 45.2 percent. But Montana State's stingy defense held the Lumberjacks to 33.3 percent shooting. MSU (11-9, 3-4 Big Sky) wasn't much better. The Bobcats shot 32.3 percent. The only worse shooting performance for NAU (12-8, 5-2) was a 32.1 showing at nationally-ranked Arizona in November. Bobcats guard Jason Erickson scored a game-high 19 points, but he missed the front end of a one-and-one with 1:07 left and his team trailing 54-50. After the miss, NAU's Chris Ferguson drilled a wide-open 3-pointer from the right wing to give the Lumberjacks a 57-50 lead with 43.2 seconds left. Kyle Feuerbach drained four free throws down the final minutes to seal the win for NAU. Aaron Bond scored 15 points and grabbed a game-high 12 rebounds for Northern Arizona. Nick Dissly added 11 points off the bench for the Bobcats, who lost their second straight road game. NAU hit just 8 of 34 shots in the second half after leading by eight at halftime. The Lumberjacks grabbed a season-high 50 rebounds.
